ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: MB&B 676 01 is about the ethical conduct of graduate and researchers alike and the possible topics that may occur during our careers. I would recommend this class to another student because it is informative as to providing some possible solutions in different scenarios.
I would recommend it because it is a good thought exercise that breaks up the monotony of some of our science classes.
Yes, you will be surprised how much you did not know and how many problems that you may one day face and will help you understand how to begin to solve them.
It's a good ethics course, worth your time.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It addressed topics that I am sure any researcher encounters and I am bound to run into as a progress through my profession.
Helped me greatly in understanding issues that may arise during the graduate career, hear real stories and begin to understand what to do to solve them if they ever come up.
It stimulated interesting thoughts about potential conflicts in the lab- and ways to deal with them...
This course deepened my knowledge of the pitfalls in research.
